      "description": "Offered is an exceptional 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the iconic S54 3.2L inline-six power plant. This vehicle has undergone comprehensive preventative maintenance, including the critical rod bearing replacement and a full double-VANOS overhaul using Beisan components. The chassis is structurally pristine, with a proactively reinforced rear subframe to mitigate common floor-pan fatigue. Power is delivered through a crisp Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox to the factory limited-slip differential. The exterior retains its original deep luster with zero orange peel or clear coat failure, while the interior Nappa leather remains supple with no bolster wear. Mechanical highlights include refreshed suspension bushings, Bilstein dampers, and a cooling system overhaul with a high-flow water pump. This is a turn-key, collector-grade example with a documented service history and no diagnostic fault codes.",
